# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Backend .dockerignore
# Place this file at:  Backend/.dockerignore
#
# Tells Docker which files to exclude when copying the build context.
# Keeping this list tight means faster builds and no sensitive files in image.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Build output directories — never copy these into the Docker build context
**/bin/
**/obj/

# .env files — secrets must be injected as environment variables at runtime,
# never baked into a Docker image
.env
.env.*
*.env

# Git history and GitHub Actions — not needed inside the container
.git/
.gitignore
.github/

# Visual Studio / Rider IDE files
*.user
*.suo
.vs/
.idea/
*.DotSettings

# Migration source code (already embedded in the published DLL — no need to copy)
# Comment this out if you run `dotnet ef database update` inside the container
# **/Migrations/

# README
README.md
